post_text:
The Mid-Prairie Community School District is in need of school bus drivers. Currently, we have one morning/afternoon bus route driver position open and are also in need of substitute bus drivers. Starting pay for a Mid-Prairie regular and substitute bus route driver is $92.64 per day for approximately 3-4 hours of work. A CDL (Class B) is required. Mid-Prairie will pay all costs and provide training in support of candidates working on acquiring their CDL. A $400 bonus will be paid after the new bus driver has driven 3 times for the district. In addition to salary, Mid-Prairie school bus drivers receive other benefits which also include IPERS retirement.

Persons interested in finding out more information or to start the application process should contact Transportation Director Teresa Hartley (319-646-6881), Human Resources Coordinator Carmela Ulin (319-646-6093), or Superintendent Mark Schneider (319-936-8601).

EOE/AA

shared_text:
Mid-Prairie Transportation
August 5 at 9:07 AM ¬∑

Due to the COVID pandemic and space on the buses, we have to modify our routes. As stated in chapter 285, State Aid for transportation,(1) Elementary pupils shall be entitled to transportation only if they live more than two
miles from the school designated for attendance.
(2) High school pupils shall be entitled to transportation only if they live more than three
miles from the school designated for attendance.

Due to the above information we are being forced to eliminate our two Kalona trailer park stops. If you live in this area, and your child goes to school in Wellman, they can still catch a bus at the Kalona Library or any attendance center in Kalona.

Please contact me with any questions you may have.

post_text:
Dear Parents,

This Monday, August 3rd, the Mid-Prairie School Board will hold a special meeting in the Mid-Prairie High School Gymnasium starting at 7:00 PM. The major item on the agenda is what school will look like when it starts again on August 24. To provide you with as much information as necessary before the meeting, the following website will take you to a copy of the administrative recommendations for three different learning options for students as well as other documents outlining specific details to help you understand what In-Person Learning will look like in the schools. Please remember that some of these documents are a work in progress and some details will change depending on the outcome of Monday's meeting and the changing conditions that might occur over the next 24 days.

Website URL:
https://sites.google.com/a/mphawks.org/mp-start-of-school/

Please contact me if you have any questions or concerns. Thank you.

Yours in service,
Mark Schneider
Email: mschneider@mphawks.org
Cell Phone: 319-936-8601

post_text:
On Saturday, June 13th, the communities of Riverside, Wellman, and Kalona will be hosting our 5th and FINAL "Pop Up Food Pantry" from 9:00-11:00 AM.
All distribution will be in Kalona but is open to all.
Location: Kalona - 711 A Avenue (The City Shop)
If you are experiencing food insecurity and need assistance, please stop by 711 A Avenue (The City Shop) between 9:00 - 11:00 AM. To keep social distancing, we would ask that you pull up to the location and stay in your vehicle and we will load the food box for you.
Please call your City Hall or Ryan at 319-936-9354 if you need to schedule an alternate pick up time or delivery.

Online Auction -- Mid-Prairie is selling a variety of items via an Online AUCTION. Picture is included for your reference with details in each picture description.

Questions may be emailed to jswartzentruber@mphawks.org.
Bids will be taken by email ONLY to jswartzentruber@mphawks.org from the time of the post until June 12, 2020 at 4pm.

Bidders may bid up to two times. Please include your phone number with your bid.
The highest bid agreeing to the expectations will be the Winning Bidder and will be notified by email or phone. The Winning Bidder will be expected to remove the purchased item by Friday, June 26, 2020. Checks are to be made payable to Mid-Prairie Community Schools by Tuesday, June 16, 2020 at 4pm.
The items are sold as is. The Mid-Prairie School District assumes no liability for buyers chosen use.

Please call your City Hall or Ryan at 319-936-9354 if you need to schedule an alternate pick up time or delivery.

post_text:
THANK YOU MID-PRAIRIE COMMUNITY!
Over 1,000 flowers were sold and $3,000 raised during the Mid-Prairie Home School Assistance Program Garden Club fundraiser. Within the first 12 hours the club sold out of all available flowers. Home School Assistance Program teacher Laura Mallory says she was blown away by the amount of support from the community and hopes to do this again, ‚ÄúWe are super excited by the suggested donations people have been giving for the flowers. It‚Äôs going to truly be a huge asset to our program, to enhance our outdoor education, continue to fund the sustainability of the green house, the water and electricity. We hope to put in several rain barrels around the Mid-Prairie Home School Assistance building and just continue to have growing adventures with the students.‚Äù Mallory says the next project the Garden Club will tackle is planting chrysanthemums, also known as mums, in July.

post_text: Congratulations to six Mid-Prairie Middle School students for qualifying for the Iowa State Mathleague.org Competition. Fifth graders Jack Sorrell and Ethan Schlabaugh and sixth graders Griffin Caskey, Landon Humble, Rowan Miller, and Ethan Slay earned an invite based on their performance at qualifying events earlier in the year. The competition will be held online from 4:00-7:00 pm on Wednesday, April 29th. The competition will consist of four test rounds--number sense, sprint, target, and team--and will culminate with the top-scoring contestants in a countdown round. High scoring participants at the State level will be invited to compete at the National Competition. The National Competition will either be held virtually this spring or in-person this fall, depending on coronavirus pandemic developments. This is Mid-Prairie Middle School's second year in a row having multiple students qualify for the State level competition.

post_text:
SPECIAL GIFT FOR OUR 2020 SENIORS!

To spread love and joy to our 2020 seniors, Open Road Driving School will be giving every Mid-Prairie High School senior a $25 Amazon gift card. They can safely shop online to buy a gift for themselves and have it delivered to their door! This is a great way to celebrate our seniors, bring a smile to their faces, and let them know that they are not alone! This is also a great opportunity for our organization to give back to our local community who has been so good to us.

Gift cards will be distributed at the Mid Prairie High School Parking lot on Saturday, May 2nd between the hours of 11am - 1pm. Simply drive to the parking lot and grab a gift card out of the trunk of a car (with safe social distancing, of course). If you do not have transportation, text your name and address to 319-671-2800 to get the card delivered at a later date.

We love our Mid-Prairie kids!
Open Road Driving School Team
#MPStrong
#ClassOf2020Strong
#WereInThisTogether

post_text: Congratulations to sophomore Lilou Beachy for qualifying for the Future Problem Solving International Conference for her scenario writing piece, "Fame over Friendship." Qualifying for this competition is an incredible accomplishment. Lilou is one of three representatives from the state of Iowa invited to participate in the Virtual International Conference from June 3-7. The topic for the international conference is terraforming. Scenario writing evaluations are based on creative and futuristic thinking, idea and character development, style/voice, mechanics, topic related research, and relationship to Future Scene.

post_text:
This Saturday the 18th from 9:00 - 11:00 the Communities of Kalona, Riverside and Wellman are coming together to provide and sponsor a "Pop Up Food Pantry" for those experiencing food insecurity.
The event will be hosted in Kalona at 711 A Avenue (City of Kalona Public Works Building). We will have two lines / tents set up at the East side of the shop to help move vehicles through timely and in a socially responsible way. We ask that you enter off of 6th street and come east. Please stay in your vehicle and a volunteer will ask a few questions and we will get food boxed and put into your vehicle.
Should you need emergency food, or you are unable to make the trip we can work to assist you in getting food delivered or picked up at a later time. We would ask that you call your respective City Hall and share with them your needs.
City of Kalona 656-2310 (emergency 936-9354)
City of Wellman 646-2154
City of Riverside 648-3501

City of Kalona, Iowa Government
April 3 at 5:38 PM ¬∑

PLEASE SHARE

We are going to have a ‚ÄúDrive Through Pop Up Food Pantry‚Äù on tomorrow morning from 9:00-11:00 at 711 A avenue (city shop)
We have 7 pallets of food from HACAP and other sources (Riverside Casino and Tyson foods).

Cheerios, pasta, beans, gardetta‚Äôs, 4 cases of HONEY CRISP APPLE SLICES, 2 cases of fresh sliced mushrooms, canned pears, canned tuna, Campbell‚Äôs cream of mushroom soup, tomato sauce, dried beans, 8 boxes of assorted breads.

post_text:
April 1, 2020

Dear Mid-Prairie Families,

It was truly heart-warming to see so many students, parents and community members during the Mid-Prairie employee parade on Monday evening in Kalona, Richmond and Frytown. I am looking forward to seeing many more smiling faces during our parade tonight in Wellman and West Chester.

I appreciated seeing all the families that practiced safe social distancing procedures along the parade route Monday evening. As you know, the safety and health of your children is a high priority for Mid-Prairie teachers, support staff members and administrators. Let‚Äôs continue to protect everyone‚Äôs health by keeping a safe social distance from other families as we wait and watch the parade tonight as well as during any future activities.

I want to thank you again for your patience, cooperation and understanding as we face this situation together. This is a great community and even in this troubled time, we have much to be grateful for.

We got this!

Yours in service,

Mark Schneider
Mid-Prairie Superintendent

post_text: Check out this job opportunity!
shared_text:
Mid-Prairie Transportation
February 19 at 10:26 AM ¬∑

Mid-Prairie CSD is looking for class D chauffeur sub drivers!

A class D is as follows: passenger vehicles which carry less than 16 passengers. No knowledge test required; no driving test required if you‚Äôve had a valid license and clear driving record for the previous two years.

All you need to do is go to the DOT and have your license changed to a class D. Mid-Prairie will pay you for your 17 hour online class that the State of Iowa requires for any driver.

This would be for all van, car and mini-bus routes. THIS DOES NOT REQUIRE A CDL. Pay is $16.04 per hour, with an hour minimum per route.

Please contact Teresa Hartley for more information if you are interested! (646-6881 or thartley@mphawks.org)
